worked on setting up and upgrading RHACS in the sandbox cluster. I installed the RHACS operator, created the Central instance, and connected secured clusters successfully. I verified storage and checked the central DB usage to make sure there is enough space for upgrade. I understood the upgrade path and followed the correct sequence from 4.7 → 4.8 → 4.9 → 4.10. During the upgrade, I monitored pods, events, and ensured all components were running fine. I also checked Central UI and confirmed login and cluster connectivity. I observed temporary issues like sensor version mismatch and collector pod scheduling, and worked on fixing them. I verified secured clusters were upgraded and became healthy after syncing with Central. I also learned how to take backup (DB and YAML) and understood the importance of DB backup before upgrade. Overall, the RHACS setup and upgrade in sandbox cluster were completed successfully and everything is working as expected.
